                        <decoDesc>
                            <decoNote type="illustration">Nineteen miniatures in the style associated with
                                Shiraz. </decoNote>
                            <decoNote type="decoration">Folios <locus from="3b" to="3b">3b</locus> and <locus
                                    from="4a" to="4a">4a</locus> are illuminated as a double
                                title-page. There are also illuminated headings of equally fine
                                quality on folios <locus from="29b" to="29b">29b</locus>(Khusraw u
                                Shirin), <locus from="98b" to="98b">98b</locus> (Layla wa Majnun),
                                    <locus from="147b" to="147b">147b</locus>(Haft Paykar), <locus
                                    from="203b" to="203b">203b</locus>(Iskandar Nama) and <locus
                                    from="275b" to="275b">275b</locus> (Sharaf Nama), with the
                                lettering in fine Kufic.</decoNote>
                            <decoNote type="decoration">In addition, on folios <locus from="29a"
                                    to="29a">29a</locus>, <locus from="202b" to="202b">202b</locus>,
                                    <locus from="203a" to="203a">203a</locus>, <locus from="275a"
                                    to="275a">275a</locus> and <locus from="314a" to="314a"
                                    >314a</locus> the blank spaces at the end of the poems are
                                covered with geometrical diaper designs in gold and occasional
                                touches of colour. On folios <locus from="98a" to="98a"
                                    >98a</locus>,<locus from="147a" to="147a">147a</locus> and
                                    <locus from="275a" to="275a">275a</locus> smaller spaces are
                                filled with fine floral scrollwork in gold touched with
                                colours.</decoNote>
                        </decoDesc>
                        <bindingDesc>
                            <decoNote>Original binding (rebacked, the spine lettered KHEM-SEH I
                                NIZAMI) of dark reddish-brown leather with tooled arabesque
                                medallion and pendants, partly gilt, and narrow gilt frame.
                                Doublures with medallion of fine bold cut-out work of brown leather
                                on a background of blue, green and gold.</decoNote>
                        </bindingDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <origDate calendar="#Hijri-qamari" from="1444" to="1445" cert="high"> Safar
                                849 (1445 CE).</origDate>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>The copyist has appended a colophon to each of the poems but gives
                                neither his name nor the place where the manuscript was produced.
                                The dates are between December 1444 and May 1445.
                                Khusraw u Shirin <locus from="29b" to="29b">(29b)</locus> - Monday, 5 Sha'ban 848/17 December 1444.
                                Layla wa Majnun <locus from="98b" to="98b">(98b)</locus> - Tuesday, 12 Ramazan 848/23 December 1444.
                                Haft Paykar <locus from="147b" to="147b">(147b)</locus> - Thursday, 12 Shawwal 848/22 January 1445.
                                Iskandar Nama <locus from="202b" to="202b">(202b)</locus> - Sunday, 14 Dhu'l-qua' da 848/22 February 1445.
                                Sharaf Nama <locus from="275b" to="275b">(275a)</locus> - Safar 849/May 1445. 
                            </p>
                            <p>On the upper margin of <locus from="3a" to="3a"
                                > folio 3a</locus> is the seal of a former owner, Fath 'Ali
                                b. Hidayat-allah, dated 1218/1803.</p>
                            <p>Formerly part of the collection of the Persian scholar <persName
                                    type="standard"
                                    ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/20108923/#Bland,_Nathaniel,_1803-1865"
                                    key="person_20108923">Nathaniel Bland (1803-1865)</persName>.
                                Bland’s oriental manuscripts were sold through Bernard Quaritch in
                                1866 to <persName type="standard"
                                    ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/97751058/#Crawford,_Alexander_Crawford_Lindsay,_Earl_of,_1812-1880"
                                    key="person_97751058">Alexander Lindsay, 25th Earl of
                                    Crawford</persName>.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>Purchased by Enriqueta Rylands, on behalf of the John Rylands
                                Library, in <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1901">1901</date> from
                                    <persName type="standard"
                                    ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/9985420/#Crawford,_James_Ludovic_Lindsay,_Earl_of,_1847-1913"
                                    key="person_9985420">James Ludovic Lindsay, 26th Earl of
                                    Crawford</persName>.</p>
                        </acquisition>
                    </history>
